            "caption": "Table 1: How does BERT spend its time? This is a breakdown of computation (in floating-point operations, or FLOPs) and latency (on a Google Pixel 3 smartphone) in BERT-base, reported to three significant digits. The FC layers account for more than 97% of the FLOPs and over 88% of the latency.",
            "footnote": "",
            "latex": "",
            "html": "<html>\n<table>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Stage</td>\n    <td>Module type</td>\n    <td>FLOPs</td>\n    <td>Latency</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Embedding</td>\n    <td>Embedding</td>\n    <td>0.00%</td>\n    <td>0.26%</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Encoder</td>\n    <td>FC in self-attention modules</td>\n    <td>24.3%</td>\n    <td>18.9%</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Encoder</td>\n    <td>softmax(QKT) V in self-attention modules</td>\n    <td>2.70%</td>\n    <td>11.3%</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Encoder</td>\n    <td>FC in feed-forward network layers</td>\n    <td>73.0%</td>\n    <td>69.4%</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Final Classifier</td>\n    <td>FC layers in final classifier</td>\n    <td>0.00%</td>\n    <td>0.02%</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Total</td>\n    <td></td>\n    <td>100%</td>\n    <td>100%</td>\n  </tr>\n</table>\n</html>",
